Following the draw for the quarter-finals, semi-finals, final of this season’s UEFA Champions League on Friday, below are the current highest goal scorers chasing the golden boot in the tournament. Bayern Munich striker, Robert Lewandowski, is currently the highest goal scorer in the Champions League with 11 goals. Borussia Dortmund attacker, Erling Haaland is second place with ten goals, while Bayern Munich’s Serge Gnabry, Napoli’s Dries Mertens and Tottenham’s Harry Kane have six goals respectively. Champions League top scorers: 11 goals: Robert Lewandowski (Bayern Munich). 10 goals: Erling Haaland (Dortmund). 6 goals: Serge Gnabry (Bayern Munich), Dries Mertens (Napoli), Harry Kane (Tottenham). 5 goals: Kylian Mbappé (PSG), Gabriel Jesus (Man City), Raheem Sterling (Man City), Son Heung-Min (Tottenham), Josip Ilicic (Atalanta), Mauro Icardi (PSG), Memphis Depay (Lyon), Lautaro Martínez (Inter Milan). 4 goals: Mislav Orsic (Dinamo Zagreb), Timo Werner (Chelsea), Achraf Hakimi (Inter Milan), Mohamed Salah (Liverpool), Rodrygo (Real Madrid), Quincy Promes (Ajax), Emil Forsberg, (RB Leipzig).